  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Uncertainty quantification has been performed characterising variability in blood viscosity, inlet velocity profiles, and haemolysis power-law constants via Monte Carlo sampling (1000 draws). A plan to extend this work with formal sensitivity analysis to rank the dominant input drivers is noted for a future revision; however, no sensitivity analysis artifact is linked in the current submission.",
