      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) must be reported for the primary QoI (hemolysis index) using at least three systematically refined meshes.",
      "rationale": "Three hexahedral meshes (2.1 M, 5.8 M, 14.3 M cells) were generated with refinement ratio r = 1.63. GCI for normalised hemolysis index is 3.1% on the medium mesh, within the accepted threshold. Richardson extrapolation confirms monotonic convergence. Achieved level 2 meets requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must be documented with measured inlet flow rates, rotational speeds, fluid temperature, and haematocrit levels.",
      "rationale": "Bench tests were conducted at 2, 3, 4, 5, and 6 L/min at 2500 and 3500 RPM. Temperature was maintained at 37 ± 0.5 °C. Haematocrit was 33 ± 1%. All parameters are traceable to calibrated instruments with documented uncertainty. Achieved level 2 meets requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted normalised index of haemolysis (NIH) must agree with experimental measurements within ±25% across all 5 operating points.",
      "rationale": "CFD-predicted NIH values range from 0.0031 to 0.0058 g/100 L across the 5 operating points. Experimental NIH values are 0.0029–0.0061 g/100 L. Maximum deviation is 18.4%, within the ±25% acceptance threshold. Achieved level 2 meets requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The modelled QoI (relative hemolysis index RH) must be directly mappable to the regulatory acceptance criterion and clinical endpoint.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the relative hemolysis index RH = NIH_device / NIH_predicate. This maps directly to the regulatory acceptance criterion RH < 1.0 and to the clinical endpoint of plasma-free haemoglobin elevation. Achieved level 2 meets requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
