      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; model form selection is documented.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-omega turbulence model and the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law haemolysis model are documented in the simulation plan. A formal model-form uncertainty analysis is not required at MRL 2 and is not performed in this submission."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All material and boundary-condition inputs must be documented with sources and nominal values; input uncertainty ranges must be stated.",
      "rationale": "Blood density (1056 kg/m³), dynamic viscosity (0.0035 Pa·s), haemolysis power-law constants (C = 1.8e-6, α = 1.991, β = 0.765), inlet velocity profiles, and rotational speed are fully documented. Uncertainty ranges for each input were characterised via literature review and propagated through Monte Carlo sampling as part of the UQ activity. Achieved level 2 meets requirement. Note: identification of which inputs are dominant drivers of output variance is planned for a future sensitivity analysis extension and is not included in the current package."
    },
